    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>
                    In this letter, Aline Burch writes on behalf of Mr. Woolf to Penguin Books, Ltd. informing them that they will not renew their contract for "The Common Reader" series with the publisher, citing their concern that republishing the work will affect the sales of the Uniform Edition.
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            West Drayton, Middx.
                        </placeName>
                        <date when="1948-07-08">
                            8th July, 1948.
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            <orgName key="Q1336200">Penguin Books, Ltd.</orgName>
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            West Drayton, Middx.
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <salute>
                        Dear Sir,
                    </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>
                    <persName key="Q703935">Mr. Woolf</persName> has asked me to reply </lb>
                    to your letter to him of <date>June 30</date>, </lb>
                    and to explain the position with </lb>
                    regard to <title>THE COMMON READER</title>, Series </lb>
                    I and II. We, ourselves, have just </lb>
                    been able to reprint the First Series </lb>
                    in our Uniform Edition at 7/6d. and </lb>
                    the Second Series is at the binders, </lb>
                    and <persName key="Q703935">Mr. Woolf</persName> feels that the issue of </lb>
                    a 1/6d <orgName key="Q1336200">Penguin</orgName> reprint, at the same </lb>
                    time, cannot fail to have an adverse </lb>
                    affect on the sales of the Uniform </lb>
                    Edition. In the circumstances, there- </lb>
                    fore, he would very much prefer not </lb>
                    to renew the <orgName key="Q1336200">Penguin</orgName> contracts, </lb>
                    at any rate for the present. </lb>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        Yours faithfully,
                    </salute>
                    <signed/>
                    <seg>
                        <persName key="MAPP0011">Secretary to Mr. Woolf</persName>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
